The paper deals with the problem of finding a target in an unknown environment, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of advice and the analysis of information complexity are also typical of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of the shortest path in a given terrain, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and can be related to data structures (cs.DS).
